name: places/ChIJ3QHQstIR2jERbQgjkXGZzmI/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURyME5fNWFBEAE
text: {'text': 'Bukit Batok Neighborhood Park..near Blk 204 Bukit Batok Central.. Short walk from Bukit Batok MRT station..walk past the NTUC supermarket at the ground floor of the station..down the escalator and turn LEFT AND walk along bukit batok central road..about 10 mins...cross the road towards blk 204. At the base of this HILL park, there is along flight of steps to get to the "nature bridge" a steel bridge built to walk along the cliff and large wood, plank surfaced   platform or deck ( some sheltered portions) to rest at the top of the "hill". It looks more like a resort!. A good view of the region from the top. A few senior citizens can be seen tending to the plants at the top. On a Saturday morning there were about 10 to 15 people exercising.', 'languageCode': 'en'}
